title: Oct. 3: Marist roundup
text: Posted Oct. 4, 2015 @ 2:00 am Posted Oct. 4, 2015 @ 2:00 am » Social News Football San Diego 30, Marist 27 Cornwall’s Mike White completed 13-of-28 for 237 yards, two touchdowns and three interceptions for Marist as the Red Foxes fell short against the Toreros. Juston Christian caught a 77-yard touchdown pass from White on a one-play drive that brought the game to 30-27 with 5:05 left. It wasn’t enough. Anthony Lawrence was 23-of-35 with a touchdown to lead San Diego, which came back from a 20-7 deficit. Garrett Clay culminated Marist’s early success with a 1-yard touchdown run, which gave the Red Foxes their 20-7 lead with 11:10 left in the second quarter. Lawrence Dickens caught a pair of touchdowns for Marist. He finished with three catches for 76 yards. Marist (1-4) travels Saturday to Campbell. Men's soccer Marist 2, Saint Peter’s 0 Marist’s SimonLund Jorgenson scored in the 87th minute, and Cameron Harr scored in the 90th. Both scored on penalty kicks. Mark Rajovic had six saves. The Red Foxes’ record is 5-5, 3-0 MAAC. Women's volleyball Marist 3, Canisius 1 Scores: 22-25, 25-10, 25-19, 25-21 Marist: Kelsey Lahey 4 service aces, 13 kills; Lexi Millington 22 digs; Amanda Schlegel 30 assists. Marist’s record is 10-6, 3-2 MAAC. recordonline.com Posted Oct. 4, 2015 @ 2:00 am » Comment or view comments
